B. Factor-of-Two Theorem for Critical Sets
Suppose that {S1, S2} is a partition of a critical set, and let
H¯ denote the measurement matrix after removing the meters in
S1 ∪ S2 from the network. Since S1 ∪ S2 is a critical set, H¯ has
rank n − 1, and the dimension of its null space is one. Let Δx
denote a unit basis vector of the null space of H¯. Recalling the
discussion in Section IV-B, if S1 is the set of adversary meters,
and S2 is the set of framed meters, then the framing attack
aligns the attack vector along H1Δx, where H1 is the m × n
matrix obtained from H by replacing the rows corresponding
to the meters in S2 with zero row vectors (H2 is defined in the
same way by replacing the rows of H corresponding to S1 with
zero row vectors.)
